str_fl_o: High priority: Comprehensive evaluation and implementation of SALINITY BARRIERS to help maintain good water quality, including "sills" (i.e., "speedbumps" along the bottom of the river channel rather than complete barriers.
str_ws_o: High priority: Don't allow DWR to create a physical facility (like it's proposed Tunnel) to bypass freshwater under or around the Delta.  Continue to force it to run that water through the Delta before it exports that water.  Such a bypass is an existential threat to Delta water quality and everything that depends on that quality, including the entire environmental ecosystem of the Delta and the Bays.  It is the worst possible climate adaptation strategy for the Delta.
missing_org_name._1: Generally, I would like to get more involved in this topic.  Unfortunately, my workload is overwhelming.  Thus, no specific organization but more generally involved with the organizations that are working on Delta adaptation matters.

str_ag_o: Related to the "building a sustainable, equitable food system" strategy -- I think that working towards a massive cultural shift that encourages folks to eat food that requires less water is critically important. That obviously goes far beyond a regional or even state-wide strategy, but given how much water goes to ag, we need a shift in the type of ag that is demanded by consumers and that will only come with major shifts in cultural norms and values.
